## 🔀 Step 3 — Submit a Pull Request

1. Go back to your forked repo's main page
2. Click **"Contribute"** → **"Open pull request"**
3. Click **"Create pull request"**
4. For the title write:
```
Add babushankar.is-a.dev
```
5. In the description box, write something like:
```
Requesting babushankar.is-a.dev for my embedded engineer portfolio
hosted at babushankar.github.io
```
6. Click **"Create pull request"**

⏳ The is-a.dev team will **review and merge** your PR — usually within **a few hours to 1 day**.

---

## ⚙️ Step 4 — Add CNAME to Your GitHub Pages Repo

While waiting for approval, do this in your **portfolio repo**:

1. Go to your portfolio repo on GitHub
2. Click **"Add file"** → **"Create new file"**
3. Name it exactly (no extension):
```
CNAME
```
4. Inside the file, type only this one line:
```
babushankar.is-a.dev
```
5. Click **"Commit new file"**

---

## 🌐 Step 5 — Configure GitHub Pages Custom Domain

1. Go to your portfolio repo → **"Settings"**
2. Click **"Pages"** in the left sidebar
3. Scroll to **"Custom domain"**
4. Type: `babushankar.is-a.dev`
5. Click **"Save"**
6. ✅ Check **"Enforce HTTPS"** (appears after a few minutes)

---

## ✅ Step 6 — Wait & Test

Once your Pull Request is **merged** by the is-a.dev team:

1. Wait **5–10 minutes** for DNS to propagate
2. Open your browser and visit:
```
https://babushankar.is-a.dev
```
🎉 Your portfolio is now live on your custom subdomain!

---

## 🔍 How to Check PR Status

- Go to **[github.com/is-a-dev/register/pulls](https://github.com/is-a-dev/register/pulls)**
- Search your username to find your PR
- GitHub will email you when it's merged

